#Repl.it exercises
#6.1 While: List of Squares - For a given integer N, print all the squares of positive integers where the square is less than or equal to N, in ascending order.

number =100 # this is the limit to count to
i=1 #the is the start of the counting ,beginning at 1
while((i*i)<=number):  
    print(i**2, end= " ")
    i +=1

  #as long as the while loop is number, print the number squared and iterate again
